column12:
You like being confused; Like complicated apps, that require hours of climbing the learning curve; Like not having Siri work, or recognize what you say (Siri can only control one room and one scene at a time); Like having random lights be ignored; Do not want to control individual lights; Like having an app that has severe limits (you can only turn on/off a maximum of 4 "rooms" when you set a wake up, auto off or auto on setting - so you are screwed if you have Hue in more than that); Feel you wasted your time setting up scenes (news flash, your old scenes are gone and you cannot create new ones);

This is one of the worst apps I have. I will stick with gen1, at least it worked

Best advice for Phillips: Terminate the idiots that thought this was a "good" idea, and the next developer needs to live in a house that has more than 3 bulbs in one room.
